{{wikipedia}}
===Etymology===
From French [[visir]], [[vizir]], or Spanish [[visir]], from Turkish [[vezir]], from Arabic {{ARchar|[[وزير]]}} (wazīr) ‘helper, aide, minister’.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/vɪˈzɪə/, /ˈvɪzɪə/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
# A high-ranking [[official]] or [[minister]] in an Islamic [[government]], especially in the [[Ottoman Empire]].

====Derived terms====
* [[vizierate]]
* [[vizierial]]
* [[viziership]]

